title: Tiddler Link Label Demo
caption: Tiddler Link Label
tags: TableOfContents [[Simple Outline Demo]]
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Demonstrates the `tiddler-link-label` attribute with wikitext.  The label is rendered as inline wikitext, so transclusions and HTML entities work — not just plain text.

The first outline below uses a core SVG icon as the link label via `tiddler-link-label="{{$:/core/images/link}}"`.  The second uses the 🔗 emoji via its HTML entity (`&#x1f517;`).

!! SVG icon label

<$simple-outline class="outline" tiddler-link="yes" tiddler-link-label="{{$:/core/images/link}}" open-depth="1" text="""
!! Theoretical Foundations

  Mathematical Precursors
    + note-boole-algebra
    + note-babbage-engine

  Computability Theory
    + note-turing-machines
    + note-church-lambda

!! The First Machines (1940s)

  + note-colossus
  + note-eniac
  + note-von-neumann-architecture
"""/>

!! HTML entity label

<$simple-outline class="outline" tiddler-link="yes" tiddler-link-label="&#x1f517;" open-depth="1" text="""
!! Operating Systems

  Academic Origins
    + note-multics

  Bell Labs Breakaway
    + note-unix-origins
    + note-c-language
    + note-thompson-ritchie
"""/>
